E&C is an international energy procurement consultancy. We guide large international companies in buying energy across the globe. That means setting up strategies for buying and greening that energy, negotiate contracts with energy suppliers, set up and run risk management programs and collect invoices, check and analyze them, calculate carbon footprints. Visit our website on www.eecc.eu to find out more about us.

We are looking for an open-minded and engaged student. We guarantee flexibility so you can combine your studies with work.

What will you do?

• Work with our international team of Data Analysts and search through internal and external data sources to find and cross-check data;
• Develop and maintain various tools (Excel, SharePoint) that allow keeping track of collected and missing data;
• Gather, arrange and input data to our data bases;
• Update portfolio reports, cross checking them for errors and adapt them for the upcoming year.

What do we offer you?

• Challenge of... working in a busy environment where handling multiple tasks is essential;
• Multiple opportunities to learn - you will be guided and trained by our most experienced data analysts;
• English language practice - you will be working mainly in English;
• Office location in Tarasy Grabiszyńskie in Wrocław and Home Office work possibilities

Job Description

Job Description

As our Product Business Analyst, you will play an integral role in shaping the future of our Live Dealer game portfolio as well as the additional services we provide to our clients.

Your responsibilities will include requirement analysis, market research, participation in product design and tactical decisions made in conjunction with our various Product Owners regarding product development, promotion and distribution. We seek an outgoing, cooperative and objective professional to add to our professional team.

Responsibilities:
• Assisting Product Owners in:
• strategic business planning and defining new projects,
• defining project goals and scope,
• improving product user experience, including user interface prototyping,
• data analysis of product performance monitoring;
• Eliciting, analysing and specifying requirements;
• Documenting requirements during the development process in a format of user stories;
• Keeping up to date product... specifications for knowledge sharing between project teams and requirements reuse;
• Participating in requirements validation, including user testing sessions;
• Supporting requirements validation, preparing information and presentations for stakeholders and team members to address questions regarding proposed product decisions;
• Assisting with communication between project teams, improving transparency, and radiating information;
• Monitoring and ensuring consistency across products;
• Advising and integrating business analysis techniques standards.

Qualifications:
• At least 3 years' experience in business analysis or a related field;
• At least a bachelor’s degree in the appropriate field of study or one of the globally-recognized certifications: CCBA, CBAP, CPRE, PBA, AAC, CFLBA;
• Advanced technical skills, excellent documentation skills;
• Experience working in Agile software development;
• Competency in Atlassian software development and collaboration tools, including JIRA and Confluence;
• Domain Knowledge in Gambling and Live games strongly preferred;
• Excellent English language communication skills;
• Ability to plan and execute requirement analysis in a logical, structured, systematic manner;
• Good leadership and social skills to mediate and cooperate well with other Evolution team members;
• Ability to work in a fast-moving, high-pressure environment whilst maintaining accuracy and attention to detail;
• Ability to operate independently, and as part of a team.

We offer:
• Challenging work on award-winning products;
• Entrepreneur culture of the company, which allows you to try new approaches and technologies all the time;
• Unbeatable recognition from the business management which translates to very competitive salaries and overall attitude;
• Bright and supportive colleagues, professionalism and opportunity for personal development.

Additional Information

About Us

Evolution is a market-leading developer and provider of products and services for online casino entertainment. Our excellence is driven by over 16,000 EVOlutioneers across 30 markets worldwide, working in product innovation, software development, IT solutions, game hosting and business support. Evolution's dynamic and creative environment creates a unique opportunity for personal and professional growth.

Our integrated business-to-business solutions guarantee that our clients can always provide an unrivalled online entertainment experience to their players globally. We thrive on remaining an award-winning digital powerhouse of entertainment products and services with an ever-expanding line-up of product brands: Evolution Live, NetEnt, Red Tiger, Ezugi, Big Time Gaming, Nolimit City and DigiWheel.

Evolution is a Swedish company founded in 2006 and listed on Nasdaq Nordic (EVO).

